<subSubSection id="C354656399601101FF37FC0FFE97FC2E" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF136E899601101FF37FC0FFE97FC2E" blockId="97.[123,652,574,1741]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">
DIAGNOSIS: The absence of a distinct pair of setal tufts on the frons easily distinguishes these beetles from others of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D6B99601101FE5DFC32FD38FC0D" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2005" box="[498,651,956,979]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrmecoides">
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA99601101FE5DFC32FD38FC0D" box="[498,651,956,979]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">myrmecoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354656399601101FF37FC78FBD1FF28" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF136E899601101FF37FC78FE00F94D" blockId="97.[123,652,574,1741]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">
DESCRIPTION: 
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA99601101FEEEFC79FEC3FBD0" box="[321,368,1015,1038]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Size</emphasis>
: Length 5.0– 
<quantity id="4CB69B0D99601101FD8EFC78FD34FBD3" box="[545,647,1014,1037]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity id="4CB69B0D99601101FF67FB9AFEEFFBF5" box="[200,348,1044,1067]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.45" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="3.45" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.6 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA99601101FEC4FB9AFE5DFBF5" box="[363,494,1044,1067]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Integument</emphasis>
: Black. 
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA99601101FDF8FB9AFF09FB96" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Vestiture</emphasis>
: Pronotal, metepisternal, and sutural tufts well developed; dorsum predominantely vested with dark setae; legs predominantly vested with pale setae. 
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA99601101FE24FB07FE79FB7E" box="[395,458,1161,1184]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Head</emphasis>
: Genae and epicranium expanded, gena behind eyes wrinkled; interocular depression and frontal umbo shallow; frons, epicranium, and gena very finely punctate; eyes subspherical, moderately convex; width across eyes equal to width across pronotum (41:41); antenna as in figs. 56, 229. 
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA99601101FF4BFAD9FE8BFAB0" box="[228,312,1367,1390]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum elongate (41:45), considerably narrower than width of elytra across humeri (41:54), finely, sparsely punctate, side margin feebly arcuate, anterior transverse depression indistinct; elytra short, notably convex; elytral depth at humerus 20, greatest depth in posterior half 30; legs notably elongate, metafemur extended beyond elytral apex. 
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA99601101FE8FF9CFFE3DF986" box="[288,398,1601,1624]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Pygidium posterior margin evenly arcuate in both sexes. 
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA99601101FDE0F9D1FF51F94D" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: As in figur 212.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136E899601101FF37F917FDB6F913" blockId="97.[123,652,574,1741]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">VARIATION: The 11th antennomere varies in shape (compare figs. 56, 229).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136E899601101FD77FF4FFBD1FF28" blockId="97.[699,1227,193,485]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">
NATURAL HISTORY: Specimens were collected during December at 
<quantity id="4CB69B0D99601101FBAFFF51FBEDFF28" box="[1024,1118,223,246]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
